title: Millie Bobby Brown: Style Diary

organizations.name: dimitrios kambouris/getty images for new york fashion week none

text: Millie Bobby Brown: Style Diary Millie Bobby Brown is 13 going on season 2 of 'Stranger Things.' The girl who always looks like an Eleven on the red carpet officially became a teenager on Feb. 19, 2017. In celebration, we've assembled our favorite looks from the starlet. The girl who always looks like an Eleven on the red carpet officially became a teenager on Feb. 19, 2017. In celebration, we've assembled our favorite looks from the starlet.  //usat.ly/2ljJhYE   Millie Bobby Brown: Style Diary None Millie Bobby Brown is 13 going on season 2 of 'Stranger Things.' The girl who always looks like an Eleven on the red carpet officially became a teenager on Feb. 19, 2017. In celebration, we've assembled our favorite looks from the starlet. Chris Pizzello/Invision/AP None Brown returned to basics while front row at the Calvin Klein Collection during New York Fashion Week on Feb. 10, 2017, pairing a black jacket with a white shirt, ripped denim and combat boots. Dimitrios Kambouris/Getty Images For New York Fashion Week None The young actress chose a red Emporio Armani gown with embellished cap sleeves for the Screen Actors Guild Awards on Jan. 29, 2017 Dan MacMedan-USA TODAY NETWORK None For an episode of 'The Ellen DeGeneres Show' that aired on Jan. 9, 2017, Brown paired black Converse with a long-sleeve dress bearing a youthful, heart pattern. Michael Rozman/Warner Bros. None She wore a sparkly Jenny Packham gown with sequinned, illusion neckline and strappy heels by Sophia Webster to the Golden Globe Awards on Jan. 8, 2017. Dan MacMedan-USA TODAY NETWORK None She wore a black and cream colorblocked dress with a bow in the back to the BAFTA Tea Party in Beverly Hills on Jan. 7, 2017. Phillip Faraone, Getty Images None Brown donned a monochromatic look to an event at the Chateau Marmont on Jan. 5, 2017 in Los Angeles, pairing a black dress by Kate Spade with matching ballet flats. Michael Kovac, WireImage None Brown accessorized a floral Kate Spade floor-length dress with glittery heels at UNICEF's 70th anniversary event at United Nations Headquarters on Dec. 12, 2016 in New York City. Noam Galai, WireImage None Her style took flight at the Emmys on Sept. 18, 2016, when she sported an enchanting Red Valentino gown with birds. Steve Granitz, WireImage None Brown paired a graphic tee with a plaid Burberry skirt and black ankle boots for an appearance on 'The Late Show with Stephen Colbert' on Sept. 13, 2016. Scott Kowalchyk/CBS None Brown sported a multi-print dress and pale pink varsity jacket while sitting with (left to right) Emma Roberts, her 'Stranger Things' co-star Winona Ryder, and Chloe Grace Moretz at the Coach Spring 2017 show on Sept. 13, 2016, in New York. Christopher Smith/Invision/AP None With her 'Stranger Things' co-stars during an episode of 'The Tonight Show,' Brown wore a white Burberry dress with black piping on Aug. 31, 2016. Andrew Lipovsky/NBC None She dressed casually in overalls and sneakers during the BUILD Speaker Series at AOL Studios on Aug. 31, 2016, in New York. Evan Agostini/Invision/AP None To the premiere of 'Stranger Things' at Mack Sennett Studios on July 11, 2016 in Los Angeles, Brown wore a voluminous high-low gown and metallic sneakers.
